The article discusses the importance of promoting and strengthening America's tradition of outdoor recreation on public lands during "Made in America Week." The Department of the Interior is hosting a roundtable with outdoor recreation industry leaders to brainstorm innovative ideas for enhancing the outdoor experience on public lands. The All-American Outdoor Experience not only represents a part of American identity but also serves as a significant economic driver, generating $887 billion in consumer spending and supporting 7.6 million American jobs. The article emphasizes the unique appeal of American parks and public lands, which attract millions of visitors each year. The author calls for unity and pride in supporting American businesses and engaging in American outdoor traditions.